    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9658893d_c78b74d8",
        "filename": "resultdb/cli/cmd_stream.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 60,
      "author": {
        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-05-31T19:57:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In this program, reservePeriodSecs is # of the total seconds reserved for the rdb process and all the descendant processes to clean up. e.g., result_adapter, content_browser, gtest, etc.\n\n1 second may be too short. What about 3 sec? If the child process finishes early upon receiving a signal, then rdb process would terminate before the reserved period passed.\n\nAnother consideration is to adjust the deadline with a shorter period before the child process. Let\u0027s say that result_adapter adopted lucictx.Deadline. Shortening the deadline for the child process will minimize the chance of sigkill-ing result_adapter process. That said, I believe the change can be made separately, when result_adapter adopts lucictx.deadline.\n(it will effectively make the bottommost command be the only one that can be sig-killed)\n\nThat said, such a change can be made in a separately when result_adapter adopts lucictx.Deadline, if this sg and you are planning to update result_adapter.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 56,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 60,
        "endChar": 1
      },
      "revId": "0d6216203b850f441f50cb79346bbb9a7aa113e4",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f6d2feed_70eec5d4",
        "filename": "resultdb/cli/cmd_stream.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 60,
      "author": {
        "id": 1118104
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-06-01T18:18:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It was my understanding (and what I saw in adhoc testing) that having a 1 second reserve meant that rdb-stream, upon receiving an interrupt forwards it immediately to the child (result_adapter), and (30 - 1) seconds later, it will cancel cmdCtx, and this cancellation will sigkill the child. Then, it\u0027s only rdb-stream that has to clean-up in that remaining second.\n\nThough 3 seconds seems reasonable even for this, so I am changing it as you suggest.",
      "parentUuid": "9658893d_c78b74d8",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 56,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 60,
        "endChar": 1
      },
      "revId": "0d6216203b850f441f50cb79346bbb9a7aa113e4",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3882afa5_1ad49e83",
        "filename": "resultdb/cli/cmd_stream.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 278,
      "author": {
        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-05-31T19:57:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Maybe, you could switch{} the channel item to print more detailed log messages. This should send a signal regardless of the reason, but without those messages, we won\u0027t exactly know the reason of a given process terminating.\n\n```\nswitch event :\u003d \u003c-lucictx.SoftDeadlineDone(cmdCtx); {\ncase event \u003d\u003d lucictx.ClosureEvent:\n  log(\"The parent context was cancelled.\")\ncase event \u003d\u003d lucictx.InterrupteEvent:\n  log(\"Received an interrupt.\")\ncase event \u003d\u003d lucictx.TimeoutEvent:\n  log(\"Soft-deadline exceeded.\")\n}\n\nlog(\"Sending an interrupt to the child process; will force kill in ~%s\", ...)\n......\n```",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 277,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 278,
        "endChar": 10
      },
      "revId": "0d6216203b850f441f50cb79346bbb9a7aa113e4",
